definition.value: A monohydroxyflavone that is  flavone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 and a methoxy group at position 7 respectively.

A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole substituted by (methoxycarbonyl)amino and butyl groups at positions 2 and 5, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of microtubule assembly and also exhibits anthelminthic activity.
An anthraquinone that is 9,10-anthraquinone in which the hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by a methyl group.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is  tectorigenin substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
